-- Ryder Cup to Restart After Seven-Hour Rain Delay With Europe in Lead
-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 2010-10-01T15:01:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/ryder-cup-to-restart-after-seven-hour-rain-delay-with-europe-in-lead.html
The 38th Ryder Cup will restart at 5
p.m. local time after rain and water on the course stopped play
after just two hours this morning.  Chief referee John Paramor said officials will try to get
in several hours of play today at Celtic Manor in Newport,
Wales.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
